div.p:
IIdly. Of the Time and Measure, When and How far we
ought so to do; 
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               . As we have Opportunity;
According to our Ability; for so also that Phrase
may well enough be understood.

Then shall he also say unto them on the Left-hand;
                  Ver. 41, &c.
Depart from me ye Cursed, into everlasting Fire, prepared
for the Devil and his Angels. FOR I was an Hungred,
and ye gave me no Meat; I was Thirsty, and ye gave
me no Drink; I was a Stranger, and ye took me not in;
Naked, and ye cloathed me not; Sick, and in Prison,
and ye visited me not.
